{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is module handoff: three source clients -> aggregation/composition layer -> summary-generation input. A unit test of one function can miss wiring/field-mapping omissions across modules. Real OS/network/LLM behavior is not required to reproduce this specific failure.","test_description":"Run the report pipeline in-process with stubbed responses for metrics, issue tracker, and deployment log adapters; intercept the payload sent to summary generation and assert all three source sections/keys are present and correctly mapped.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is cross-module error propagation/fallback behavior (source adapter failure -> report assembler continues -> section note injected). It does not require real network or subprocess behavior; an in-process failing adapter reproduces the failure mode.","test_description":"Execute in-process with two normal source adapters and one adapter that raises a timeout/unavailable error; assert run completes, report contains the unavailable note for that source, and other sections are still populated.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on model output quality (faithful representation of key values). A stubbed/deterministic fake would hide hallucination, omission, or distortion failures. No multi-step agent chain is required here, so Workflow is not the minimum.","test_description":"Run summary generation against the real model with representative fixtures; evaluate factual consistency between input key metrics/incidents/deployments and generated narrative using strict acceptance checks (must include/align with critical values, no contradictions). Repeat across runs to detect model variance-related failures.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This behavior explicitly requires real external boundaries: source APIs plus real email transport/inbox delivery. In-process mocks can pass while masking SMTP/API auth, transport, or inbox-delivery failures. Higher level rejected: behavior text validates end-to-end delivery, not LLM decision quality or multi-agent sequencing.","test_description":"Run the scheduled/report job in an environment using real endpoints (or production-like reachable services) and real email delivery to a test mailbox; verify report generation completes and the delivered email appears in the configured recipient inbox with expected subject/body structure.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.73,"Agentic":0.14,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"The failure mode spans real infrastructure boundaries: email service unreachability, local filesystem persistence, and cross-run retry behavior. Mocking these can hide real failures (write durability/path permissions/process restart/scheduler timing). No model-quality dependency is required.","test_description":"Induce real email delivery failure (unreachable endpoint), run job and assert report is persisted to local fallback file; then restore email service and execute next scheduled run, asserting previously saved report is retried and delivered successfully.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.17,"System":0.74,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.03}}]}
